A body of
an Ekurhuleni Metro police officer was discovered earlier today on the side of
the road in Reige Park, Ekurhuleni next to Ramaphosa informal settlement. The
officer’s body was found along Elsburg road. Police
spokesman, Captain Mavela Masondo confirmed that they were called to the area
following the discovery of the body. “Police
were called by the community in the Ramaphosa area.” He said
when police arrived, a dead person was wearing Ekurhuleni Metro Police uniform “He had
bullet wounds on the upper body. The motive of the killing is currently
unknown.” Masondo
said they appealing to anyone who might have information that can lead to the
arrest of the suspect to come forward.